sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K843007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The device inhibits cell division after it reaches a critical level. For this we used MinC as the cell division inhibitor. The critical level can be changed by changing the promoter before the LuxI region.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Berke G??rkan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had no considerations during the design of the sequence

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K843005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The part contains 3OC6HSL Sender device (BBa_F1610) controlled by BBa_J23116 constitutive promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Berke G??rkan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We had no design considerations for this part

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K843006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: 3OC6HSL Receiver Device activated MinC cell inhibiton system
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The part is the second half of Cell Limiter system iGEM METU 2012 team designed. By quorum sensing the part is able to stop cell division and have a stable amount of cells in the work environment.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Berke G??rkan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no design considerations

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_F1610
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device accepts PoPS as input and produces the LuxI enzyme. This enzyme produces 3OC<sub>6</sub>HSL.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Caitlin Conboy and Jennifer Braff

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_F2621
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This device senses the 3OC<sub>6</sub>HSL concentration in the media and produces output PoPS according to the transfer function given below. LuxR production is controlled by the LuxR controllable R0063.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Barry Canton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: luxI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Synthesizes 3OC6HSL, which binds to LuxR.

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux repressor, LuxR. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound HSL. This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: An LVA tail (sequence: AANDENYALVA) was added to increase protein degradation. .

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lux pL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The left promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is down-regulated by the action of the Lux repressor, LuxR. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription from Pr, repressing transcription from Pl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
This promoter is based on the Vibrio fischeri quorum sensing gene promoters. Two genes LuxI and LuxR and transcribed in opposite directions as shown below. The original sequence from which the parts BBa_R0062 and BBa_R0063 were derived is shown in the picture below.Includes most of Lux reulatory region, including the LuxR binding site which activates the right promoter. A putative LuxR autorepression binding site is also identified adjacent to the -10 site of the right promoter. This 2nd site has 55% identity with the first site. Putative inverted repeats (of size 18-27 bp) also exist between these two sites (not marked above), which may represent binding sites for other regulatory proteins.

Unspecified.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K299806

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: MinC under too strong RBS and strong promoter inhibits cell divisions in uncontrolled manner. Thus no transformant are generated using following construct: pT7-B0034-minC in BL21.
